# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored — never commit real secrets.
# v2.2 = WORKER transport (a Python Bot-API worker runs `claude -p` per message;
# no `claude --channels`, no tmux). All state lives on ONE volume: ~/.claude.
# Flow: docker compose up -d  →  provide auth (below)  →  done.

# ===== REQUIRED =====
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=123456:put-your-botfather-token-here
OWNER_ID=<your-telegram-user-id>

# ===== Auth (Claude SUBSCRIPTION — the worker never uses a metered API key) =====
# PRIMARY: a long-lived OAuth token (recommended for headless). Create once with
#   `claude setup-token` and paste the sk-ant-oat01-... it prints:
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=sk-ant-oat01-...
# OR log in interactively once (creds persist on the ~/.claude volume):
#   docker exec -it -u botuser <container> claude auth login
# NOTE: ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is intentionally IGNORED — the worker pops it so every
#   turn runs on the subscription. Don't rely on it for auth.

# ===== Worker permission + tools =====
# TG_WORKER_PERMISSION_MODE = the `claude -p --permission-mode` the worker passes.
#   Valid: default | acceptEdits | bypassPermissions | plan. Aliases: auto->acceptEdits,
#   manual->default, empty->acceptEdits. (Falls back to PERMISSION_MODE if unset.)
# PERMISSION_MODE=auto
# TG_WORKER_PERMISSION_MODE=acceptEdits
#
# TG_WORKER_ALLOWED_TOOLS = comma list passed to `--allowedTools`. DEFAULT (safe for
#   group-exposed bots, NO free Bash):
#     mcp__mempalace,Read,Grep,Glob,WebFetch,WebSearch
#   Widen ONLY for trusted personal bots, e.g. add Bash / Edit / Write / mcp__playwright:
# TG_WORKER_ALLOWED_TOOLS=mcp__mempalace,Read,Grep,Glob,WebFetch,WebSearch,Bash,Edit,Write

# ===== Specialized bot (role profile) =====
# BOT_ROLE = boot the bot into a delivery-workflow role. Seeds the role's CLAUDE.md +
#   settings + rules (layered on the base) on first run. Values: ba|planner|dev-fe|
#   dev-be|tester|infra. EMPTY / unset / default = default behavior. See roles/README.md.
# BOT_ROLE=ba

# ===== Optional =====
# MODEL=sonnet
# TZ=Asia/Ho_Chi_Minh   # reminder scheduler fires on this local time (image default)
